race.comment: MANIFEST THE MILLI (4) on top. He's certainly had a few chances but is knocking on the door, working home from midfield to just miss at Seymour in a good effort behind Azazel who has since run well at Listed level. Back in trip here is the query but the big track will suit and he'll be strong late. BLUE COWBOY (1) resumes. He showed promise last time in with the first two efforts especially good. Tipping he makes improvement this time in kicking off at a suitable trip. NEWCOMBE (5) resumes. He got over a bit more ground last time in, narrowly beaten here over 1717m before a spell. He'll likely get back but if the tempo is on, he'll be finishing hard. RACEY CASEY (10) put in a good effort at Warrnambool last time out and can improve out in trip. FORTYSECONDSTREET (8) was well beaten fresh at Benalla but has upside and can do much better.
